The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, July 02, 2004 				 Life for killer husband, jail for parents 
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Howrah, July 1: Baishakhi Das was 13 when 24-year-old Manoj Praharaj wooed her away from home on her way to school. They married in December 1998.																								Four years later, Manoj and his parents killed the girl and hanged the body from the ceiling of a room, bringing to an end torture that had started soon after the marriage. Though Manoj had eloped, he wanted Baishakhi to bring him dowry. 																								Today, a Howrah court sentenced Manoj Praharaj of Andul to life term for murdering his child wife. His mother was jailed for 10 years and father seven.																								It was a rare and very cruel crime, said Mrinal Kanti Chowdhury, the third additional district and sessions judge. In cold blood, they killed the girl and hanged her body. There is no manner of doubt about the gravity of the charges. The punishment should be severe, he said.																								Baishakhis father Bidhan Das said he had rushed to the Praharajs hearing about the marriage. Manojs mother Basanti had assured him that she would live with us like our daughter. Please do not go to police and complain against my son. It was not long before repeated demands for money began coming.
